    title: "Predictive Policing in the City of Chicago"
    authors:
      - family-names: "Lachérade"
        given-names: "P."
      - family-names: "Szabo"
        given-names: "B."
      - family-names: "Krikava"
        given-names: "J."
      - family-names: "Aeby"
        given-names: "M."
    year: "2021"
    url: "https://github.com/marquito95/Predictive-policing-Chicago"
    notes: "SciencesPo 'Decoding Biases in AI' project auditing Chicago's Strategic Subjects List for racial bias. morie's predictive-policing calibration audit (morie.fairness.predpol) is an independent clean-room reimplementation of this project's published methodology -- no code copied."
